{
  "texts": [
    "This crucial step towards the real-world application of AI-driven rehabilitation solutions cannot be underestimated, particularly when considering their translation into clinical settings.",
    "The transition from a controlled experimental environment to the complex and dynamic conditions of a clinical context demands rigorous validation to ensure both the efficacy and safety of AI-based algorithmic solutions.",
    "The gap between simulation-based or healthy-subject validation and clinical implementation underscores a critical concern.",
    "It emphasizes that the bridge between research and practical clinical deployment necessitates robust human-centered validation studies, ideally involving individuals who are representative of the target patient population.",
    "Moreover, a notable gap within the current literature pertains to the integration of human-centered technologies."
  ]
}